For the minimum distribution time for client-server distribution, we use the formula given in the textbook:

Dcs = max (NF/Us, F/dmin)

Where, F = 15 Gbits
Us = 30 Mbps
dmin = di = 2 Mbps


                  N
                10       100     1000
    300 Kbps    7680    51200   512000
u   700 Kbps    7680    51200   51200
    2000 Kbps   7680    51200   51200


For the minimum distribution time for P2P distribution, we use the following formula:

Dp2p = max (F/Us, F/dmin, NF/(Us + sum(Ui)))


                  N
                10       100     1000
    300 Kbps    7680    25904   47559
u   700 Kbps    7680    15616   21525
    2000 Kbps   7680    7680    7680


